content.description:
Typical

Uinta

face climbing up a small broken crack. Insecure climbing to a sketchy and loose ledge sum up this route.

Climb the natural line up, and lightly left. Protection is good, but sparse. Finish at a shared chain anchor.

Did you bring gear?

Do it!
content.protection: A set of small/micro cams and a full set of small to medium stoppers.
content.location:
Natasha

is the right-most natural crack line on the right-side face. It starts about 15 left of a large broken dihedral.

content.description:
All of the rating, this spicy line starts hard off the ground climbing a steep bulge to a shallow ledge. From the ledge follow the obvious right-leaning crack through a small cut, aiming right for a small relief in the face.

Sustained climbing with good protection that can be hard to place.  Finish on a ledge a shared chain anchor.
content.protection: A small single rack and stoppers.
content.location: On the left side of the wall, this is the only clean, right-leaning crack on the face.
